# Netlify _redirects — copied verbatim into dist/ by Vite.
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS
# The npm `pyodide` package ships only the core runtime (pyodide.js,
# pyodide.asm.wasm, python_stdlib.zip, pyodide-lock.json). It does NOT
# ship the package wheels (micropip, packaging, numpy, pandas, ...).
# Pyodide expects to fetch those at runtime. When `indexURL` is set to a
# self-hosted path like /pyodide/, the wheels 404, and Netlify's SPA
# rewrite then serves index.html with 200 OK in their place. Pyodide
# treats that as a successful fetch with the wrong bytes, the SRI
# integrity check fails, and loadPackage errors out.
#
# The rule below: when a file under /pyodide/ doesn't exist locally,
# 301-redirect the request to the canonical jsdelivr Pyodide CDN. SRI
# passes because the CDN serves the bytes pyodide-lock.json hashes
# against. Files that DO exist locally (pyodide.js, .wasm, .zip,
# pyodide-lock.json) are served straight from this origin — Netlify
# checks file existence before applying redirect rules.
#
# IMPORTANT NETLIFY SYNTAX NOTE
# A splat (*) can ONLY appear at the END of the source path. So
# `/pyodide/*.whl` is INVALID and is silently ignored — that bug shipped
# in commit a7fa5f3 and was the reason the previous deploy still failed.
# This rule uses `/pyodide/*` (splat at end), which is valid.
#
# Bump the version segment whenever you upgrade the pyodide npm package.

/pyodide/*   https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/pyodide/v0.26.4/full/:splat   301

# SPA fallback for the agent UI. Must come AFTER the /pyodide/ rule.
/*   /index.html   200
